Another round leather ball Attacker  Ifeanyi George  wth Nigerian Professional Football League has been lost to the cold hands of death following an auto accident that claimed the life of Rangers’ player,National Daily learnt.
Sadly, his death comes a month after the killing of Remo Stars’ Tiamiyu Kazeem and barely two weeks after another player of Nasarawa United player, Chineme Martins who slumped and died during a league match.
Ifeanyi, according to a tweet from the Rangers’ handle died this Sunday 22 March when his car had an accident on his way from Enugu to Lagos.






			
